| Possible airburst swarm / tsunami    | 12.8–12.7      | Cosmic fragments / ice-sheet steam explosions                                 | 20–40 m trans-Atlantic run-up |
| Melt-Water Pulse 1B (supercharged)     | 12.4–11.4      | Ice-sheet collapse accelerated by cosmic-ray forcing                             | Final 60–80 m eustatic rise |
| Combined relative sea-level jump        | 12.8–11.4      | 130–170 m effective drowning of the shelf in < 800 years                         | Entire coastal empire erased |

## 3. Göbekli Tepe – The Direct Refugee Offshoot
| Evidence                                   | 2023–2025 Data                                                                 | Validation for Atlantis |
|--------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------|
| Construction timing                          | 11.6–10.8 ka cal BP (58 new dates, 2024)                                      | Immediate post-12 ka response |
