| Vulture / bird symbolism + skull cult             | Dominant motifs (Pillar 43, 18, 33)                                              | Western-afterlife ideology carried inland |
| Deliberate burial of sites                    | All enclosures intentionally back-filled ~8200 BCE                                  | Classic “knowledge ark” after civilisation-ending flood |
| Sudden appearance, no local precursors          | Appears fully formed in Upper Mesopotamia                                        | Refugee population influx |
| Astronomical record on Pillar 43               | Lunisolar calendar + possible comet/airburst record ~10 950 BCE                       | Same sky-watching priesthood that tracked the 12 ka cycle |

→ Göbekli Tepe is the **inland memory vault** built by survivors of the same catastrophe that drowned the Richat empire.

## 4. The Moving-Pillars Mechanism
